          content. Every recipe has been tested in a physical kitchen by real people to ensure accurate flavor balances
          and cooking instructions.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        When you browse our website, we collect minimal data to improve your experience. This includes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Device Information:</strong> We automatically collect details about your web browser, IP address,
          time zone, and cookies installed on your device to ensure optimal site rendering.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Patterns:</strong> We collect data on which product catalog pages and blog articles you visit,
          along with search queries, to understand which spices and recipes are most popular.</li>
        <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> If you voluntarily submit your email to join our newsletter or product
          waitlists, we store that address securely in our database.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>
        We utilize the collected information to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Optimize and customize your browsing layout;</li>
        <li>Deliver culinary newsletters, cooking guides, and recipes (if subscribed);</li>
        <li>Notify you when a popular out-of-stock product has been freshly ground and replenished;</li>
        <li>Screen website traffic for potential security risks or spam.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Data Security & Storage</h2>
      <p>
        Your trust is paramount. Any personal data collected (such as waitlist emails) is stored securely in our MongoDB
